quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,But does he not know that when what are in the graves are scattered
  100,10,and the hearts' contents are retrieved
  100,11,"on that Day, their Lord is fully knowledgeable"
  101,1,The striking calamity
  101,2,What is the striking calamity
  101,3,And how would you know what is the striking calamity
  101,4,It is the Day when the human beings will be like dispersed moths
  101,5,and the mountains will be like fluffed up wool
  101,6,"and then, the one whose scales are heavy [with good deeds]"
  101,7,will have a pleasant life
  101,8,but the one whose scales are light
  101,9,his refuge will be an abyss
  101,10,And what will convey to you what that is
  101,11,a Raging Fire
  102,1,Your greed for more has distracted you
  102,2,until you go down to your graves
  102,3,"No, indeed you will soon know"
  102,4,Certainly you will soon know
  102,5,"Indeed, If you knew the knowledge of certainty"
  102,6,you would see Hell
  102,7,then you would surely see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,And on that Day you will be asked about the pleasures you enjoyed
  103,1,I swear by the Late Afternoon
  103,2,"the human being is surely, in a state of loss"
  103,3,Except for those who have believed and done good deeds and urged one another to the Truth and urged one another to patience
  104,1,Woe to every scorning backbiter
  104,2,who has amassed wealth and diversified it
  104,3,thinking that his wealth will make him immortal
  104,4,No! He will surely be thrown into the Crusher
  104,5,And what will convey to you what is the Crusher
  104,6,It is the kindled Fire of God
  104,7,reaching right into the hearts
  104,8,it will engulf them
  104,9,in extended columns
  105,1,Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the army who had Elephants
  105,2,Did He not utterly bring their perfect planning to nothing
  105,3,And He sent birds in flocks against them
  105,4,striking them with stones of hard clay
  105,5,He made them like eaten straw
  106,1,So that Quraysh remains secure
  106,2,They are secure in their Winter and Summer journeys
  106,3,Let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,"who has fed them after hunger, and made then safe after fear"
  107,1,Have you seen the one who denies this faith
  107,2,For that is the one who drives the orphan away
  107,3,and does not encourage the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who pray
  107,5,"but, who do not pay attention to their prayer"
  107,6,"Those who make a show [of their deeds]"
  107,7,and withhold assistance to others
  108,1,We have given you all that is good in abundance
  108,2,so pray to your Lord and sacrifice for Him
  108,3,Your enemy is the one who is cut off
  109,1,"Say: \"You who deny the truth"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,and you do not worship what I worship
  109,4,and I will never worship what you worship
  109,5,Neither will you worship what I worship
  109,6,"You have your own religion, and I have mine"
  110,1,"When God's victory has come, together with His conquest"
  110,2,and you see people embracing God's religion in multitudes
  110,3,"exult your Lord's glory, and praise Him, and ask for His forgiveness; for He is ever-accepting of repentance"
  111,1,"Doomed are the hands of Abu Lahab, and he is doomed too"
  111,2,His wealth and all that he gained would not help him
  111,3,He will burn in a fire strongly glowing
  111,4,"and his wife as well, the carrier of firewood"
  111,5,Around her neck is a rope of palm fiber
  112,1,"Say: \"He is God who is Uniquely Singular"
  112,2,"Who is Eternal, [the uncaused cause of all that exists]"
  112,3,Who has not given birth nor is He born
  112,4,and there is no equivalent to Him
  113,1,"Say: \"I seek refuge with the lord of the Daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil in that which He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the darkness when it settles
  113,4,and from women who blow on knots
  113,5,and from the evil of the envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say: \"I seek refuge with the Lord of people"
  114,2,The King of people
  114,3,The God of people
  114,4,From the evil of the insidious whisperer
  114,5,"who whispers [evil] into the hearts of people"
  114,6,from among the jinn or people